{{Quote|&hellip;my very first professional comic book gig was drawing a Boba Fett story (in Star Wars Tales #18). The job was set up by one of the nicest people you'll ever meet in the industry, editor Diana Schutz, and when she asked me, "Would you like to draw Star Wars?" I (being an über Star Wars nerd) ALMOST CRIED!|Stewart McKenny, on getting asked to draw Star Wars|<ref name="fbcry">{{Facebook|username=stewart.mckenny|url=photo.php?fbid=10155193187439189&set=a.306312484188&type=3|name=Stewart McKenny|date=2017-03-10|archiveurl=https://archive.ph/ngLLq}}</ref>}}
'''Stewart McKenny''' is an [[Wikipedia:Australian|Australian]] illustrator who has worked for several major comics publishers, including [[Dark Horse Comics]] and [[Marvel Comics]]. While Dark Horse Comics was licensed to publish ''[[Star Wars]]'' content, he was the penciler for the [[Star Wars comic books|comic]] "[[Being Boba Fett]]" before doing the illustrations for the [[Star Wars: Clone Wars Adventures (graphic novels)|''Star Wars: Clone Wars Adventures'']] comics "[[Heroes on Both Sides (comic story)|Heroes on Both Sides]]," "[[The Drop (comic story)|The Drop]]," "[[Spy Girls]]," and "[[Graduation Day]]." He has been awarded honorary membership of the ''Star Wars'' costuming groups [[Rebel Legion]] and [[Mandalorian Mercs]] for his contributions to the franchise.

==Biography==

===At Dark Horse===
{{Quote|I've been a HUGE Star Wars fan since I was a little kid!|Stewart McKenny, after meeting Temuera Morrison|<ref name="FBTem">{{Facebook|username=stewart.mckenny|url=photo/?fbid=10160017445099189&set=a.229186609188|name=Stewart McKenny|date=2022-05-11|archiveurl=https://archive.ph/RRgj4}}</ref>}}
Stewart McKenny is an [[Wikipedia:Australian|Australian]] comic illustrator who has worked for major comic publishers such as [[Dark Horse Comics]] and [[Marvel Comics]].<ref name="Supa" /> He<ref name="Pronoun" /> had been a fan of ''Star Wars'' for many years, having watched [[Star Wars: Episode IV A New Hope|''Star Wars'': Episode IV ''A New Hope'']] and [[Star Wars: Episode V The Empire Strikes Back|''Star Wars'': Episode V ''The Empire Strikes Back'']] on [[Wikipedia:Betamax|Betamax]] and seeing [[Star Wars: Episode VI Return of the Jedi|''Star Wars'': Episode VI ''Return of the Jedi'']] in a cinema. While collecting figures from the franchise over the years, McKenny had been working towards employment with a major [[Wikipedia:American|American]] comic book publisher, a dream of his for years. His first job with such a publisher<ref name="FBTem" /> and first foray into the ''[[Star Wars]]'' universe began with Dark Horse Comics, working as the penciler on the short [[Star Wars comic books|comic]] "[[Being Boba Fett]]," featured in the [[Star Wars Tales 18|eighteenth issue]] of the [[2003]] ''[[Star Wars Tales]]'' comic series.<ref name="BBF" />

"Being Boba Fett" was also collected in the [[2005]] Dark Horse Comics ''Star Wars Tales'' comic book trade paperback collection's [[Star Wars Tales Volume 5|fifth volume]]<ref name="Tales5">''[[Star Wars Tales Volume 5]]''</ref> and Marvel Comics' ''[[Star Wars Legends Epic Collection: The Empire Vol. 4]]'' as part of the [[Epic Collection]] trade paperback series in [[2018]].<ref name="EpicEmpire">''[[Star Wars Legends Epic Collection: The Empire Vol. 4]]''</ref> McKenny would reminisce about this in [[2017]] ahead of the release of ''[[Star Wars: The Mandalorian]]''{{'s}} [[The Mandalorian Season Two|second season]], noting that he almost cried with excitement when approached by [[Diana Schutz]].<ref name="fbcry" /> He would meet the actor for [[Boba Fett/Legends|Boba Fett]], [[Temuera Morrison]], at a convention in [[2022]] after Morrison had signed several artworks of Boba Fett that had been drawn by McKenny. A photo of this moment was shared with the artist's fans, noting this comic was the first comic depiction of Boba Fett's adult face, based on Morrison.<ref name="FBTem" />

===The Adventures===
{{Quote|Okay&hellip; so a few years back I designed Jedi Treetower for 'Star Wars: Clone Wars Adventures'! This weekend I got the SURPRISE OF MY LIFE when the incredible folk at Rebel Legion Hoth Base presented me with my VERY OWN Jedi costume based on Treetower!|Stewart McKenny, upon receiving his Jedi costume from Australia's branch of the Rebel Legion|<ref name="FBTreetower">{{Facebook|username=stewart.mckenny|url=photo.php?fbid=10151970707454189&set=a.229186609188&type=3|name=Stewart McKenny|date=2013-10-22|archiveurl=https://archive.md/mHsv4}}</ref>}}
[[File:JediMcKenny.png|thumb|left|250px|Character designs of Treetower and McKenny wearing his Jedi costume based on the character]]
McKenny was next involved with the [[Star Wars: Clone Wars Adventures (graphic novels)|''Star Wars: Clone Wars Adventures'']] comics, a short story expansion of [[Genndy Tartakovsky]]'s animated television series ''[[Star Wars: Clone Wars]]'', with the comics utilizing the same art style used for the series. McKenny illustrated four comics in the series, two of which were published in [[2006]]. The first of these, titled "[[Heroes on Both Sides (comic story)|Heroes on Both Sides]]," appeared in the series' [[Star Wars: Clone Wars Adventures Volume 5|fifth volume]].<ref name="HoBS" />

The second, titled "[[The Drop (comic story)|The Drop]]," was published in the [[Star Wars: Clone Wars Adventures Volume 6|following volume]] and featured the [[Ugnaught/Legends|Ugnaught]] [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]] [[Treetower]].<ref name="TD">{{CWACite|6|The Drop (comic story)}}</ref> Treetower was designed by McKenny during his work on the story, and in [[2013]] he would receive his own Jedi costume based on the character from the [[Rebel Legion]] ''Star Wars'' Costume Club's Hoth Base branch,<ref name="FBTreetower" /> located in [[Wikipedia:Victoria (Australia)|Victoria]], Australia.<ref name="Hothbase">{{WebCite|url=https://rebellegion.com/baseoutpost-location/page/4|text=Base/Outpost List (page 4)|work=[[Rebel Legion]]|archivedate=20211115125724}}</ref> The next comic McKenny illustrated was "[[Spy Girls]]," published in the [[Star Wars: Clone Wars Adventures Volume 7|seventh volume]]<ref name="SG">{{CWACite|7|Spy Girls}}</ref> on [[January 31]], [[2007]].<ref name="CW7date">{{DarkHorse|url=Books/14-333/Star-Wars-Clone-Wars-Adventures-Volume-7|text=Star Wars: Clone Wars Adventures Volume 7}}</ref> The final comic he illustrated in the series was titled "[[Graduation Day]]," published in the [[Star Wars: Clone Wars Adventures Volume 10|tenth volume]]<ref name="GD">{{CWACite|10|Graduation Day}}</ref> on [[December 19]], 2007.<ref name="CW10date">{{DarkHorse|url=Books/13-624/Star-Wars-Clone-Wars-Adventures-Volume-10|text=Star Wars: Clone Wars Adventures Volume 10}}</ref>

===Recognition===
[[File:MandoMcKenney.jpg|thumb|right|250px|McKenny receives his honorary membership from the Mandalorian Mercs]]
McKenny has been a guest of Australian pop culture conventions for many years, attending events including [[Wikipedia:Supanova Expo|Supanova Expo]]<ref name="Supa" /> and [[Wikipedia:Oz Comic Con|Oz Comic Con]].<ref name="OzCC">{{WebCite|url=http://www.ozcomiccon.com/guests/stewart-mckenny|text=Stewart McKenny|work=[[Wikipedia:Oz Comic Con|Oz Comic Con]]|archivedate=20170527082208}}</ref> On [[October 21]], [[2011]], at the [[Wikipedia:Melbourne|Melbourne]] Armageddon convention, he was awarded honorary membership to the Rebel Legion.<ref name="RLartists">{{WebCite|url=https://rebellegion.com/member-roster/honorary-members/artists|text=Artists|work=[[Rebel Legion]]|archivedate=20210813160605}}</ref> Two days later, at the same convention, he was also inducted as an honorary member of the "[[Mandalorian Mercs]]" club by the Sandhawk clan,<ref name="MM">{{WebCite|url=http://mandalorianmercs.org/our-members/honorary-members|text=Honorary Members|work=[[Mandalorian Mercs]]|archivedate=20210813063725}}</ref> the Australian branch of the club.<ref name="MMclan">{{WebCite|url=https://mandalorianmercs.org/our-members/clancamp-locator|text=Clan Locator|work=[[Mandalorian Mercs]]|archivedate=20211011120656}}</ref> These honorary memberships meant McKenny joined other people who have helped shape the ''Star Wars'' universe, including cast members, crew, artists, and authors.<ref name="MM" /><ref name="RLmembers">{{WebCite|url=https://rebellegion.com/member-roster/honorary-members|text=Honorary Members|work=[[Rebel Legion]]|archivedate=20210815064949}}</ref>

